ined effect of absolute negative liquid-film pressure and accommodation\ncoefficient on the maximum mass flux feasible during transpiration. Continuum\nsimulations coupled with kinetic theory reiterate the existence of an upper\nlimit to height of trees. The numerical model developed here is adept to be\nemployed to design and advance several other nanofluidics-based natural and\nengineering systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Nov 2021 23:58:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-01"}
