ative\nbackground slowly disrupts the rapidly established polymorphism at the\nmajor-effect locus, which is confirmed by individual-based simulations. Our\nstudy highlights how segregation of a quantitative background can greatly\nimpact the dynamics of major-effect loci by provoking migrational meltdowns.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Nov 2021 12:06:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2022 14:34:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-01"}
